    • Method Detail

      • getNOnce

        public static java.lang.String getNOnce()
        Returns the generated nonce for this particular invocation. This will change on each time the page is reloaded, but will remain constant throughout a single page request. This value is what is in the Content-Security-Policy header if enabled and can be included in the script tags if strict-dynamic mode is enabled. The NOnce length default is 24 bytes (which are then Base64 encoded) but can be changed in the configuration as described in the documentation.
        Returns:
        NOnce String for this invocation.
        Since:
        1.0
